        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2008-01-29T14:45:43.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>I personally don't want the decorators to get too complex, as they become harder to maintain and document.</p>

<p>My preference will be to add a class of 'required' to labels of required elements, and a class of 'optional' otherwise; this behaviour will be the default.</p>

<p>Additionally, I'll allow setting optional decorator parameters for 'requiredPrefix' and 'requiredSuffix'; these can be arbitrary text, and would be placed between the  tags. Any functionality beyond this would be something the user would be expected to create in a custom Label decorator.</p>

        </div>
    </div>
        <div class="comment">
        <p class="metadata">Posted by Matthew Weier O'Phinney (matthew) on 2008-01-30T15:28:36.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>Resolved in r7706.</p>

<p>By default, the Label decorator now adds either the class 'optional' or 'required' to the HTML label element. Additionally, you can optionally specify any combination of the following decorator options or element attributes:</p>

<ul><li>optionalPrefix: text to prepend to label when element is optional</li>
<li>optionalSuffix: text to append to label when element is optional</li>
<li>requiredPrefix: text to prepend to label when element is required</li>
<li>requiredSuffix: text to append to label when element is required</li>
</ul>
        </div>
